\[\sin \left( \theta + \frac{\pi}{4} \right) = \sin \theta \cos \frac{\pi}{4} + \cos \theta \sin \frac{\pi}{4} = \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2} (\sin \theta + \cos \theta).\]Therefore,
